    "description": "A systematic mesh refinement study was conducted across four successively finer hexahedral meshes (0.8M, 2.1M, 5.4M, and 12.7M elements) to establish grid-independent hemolysis index predictions. Richardson extrapolation was applied to quantify discretization error. The study confirmed that the 5.4M element mesh achieves a grid convergence index (GCI) below 2% for the scalar stress-weighted exposure time integral used as the hemolysis surrogate.",
